Despite not being a regular for Brentford toward the end of the English Premier League (EPL) in the outgoing season, Frank Onyeka’s call-up to the national team for the AFCON 2023 Qualifiers against Sierra Leone has been celebrated by Brentford. In a statement issued yesterday on its website, Onyeka was described as the 50th Brentford player to have won a full international cap while playing for Brentford. Onyeka has not played for Brentford since March due to an ankle injury and missed Nigeria’s friendly against Mexico and Ecuador but was invited by the Portuguese gaffer for the tie on Thursday in Abuja.   Newcastle plans fresh ’monster  offer’ for Osimhen     Arsenal end interest in Osimhen     Peseiro retains two NPFL players for AFCON qualifiers   Super Eagles will face Sierra Leone on Thursday, 9 June, and then Sao Tome and Principe next Monday, 13 June, in their first two matches. Onyeka is expected to join the Eagles ahead of the match with Sierra Leone. With seven caps to his credit, Onyeka was part of the team to the 2022 AFCON in Cameroon and he was also part of the Nigeria team that lost a Play-Off against Ghana for a place in the 2022 FIFA World Cup, which will be held in Qatar at the end of the year. Since joining Brentford, Onyeka has earned six out of his seven caps for the former African champions.